<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id62db56d0-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s5144"><num value="5144">§ 5144.</num><heading> Certification of rental proceeds</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Notwithstanding any other provision of law, any actual rental proceeds from the lease of land acquired under <ref href="/us/usc/t25/s5136">section 5136 of this title</ref> certified by the Secretary of the Interior shall be deemed—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id62db56d1-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s5144/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> to constitute the rental value of that land; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id62db56d2-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s5144/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> to satisfy the requirement for appraisal of that land.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id62db56d3-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/109/221/tII/s203">Pub. L. 109–221, title II, § 203</ref>, <date date="2006-05-12">May 12, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/341">120 Stat. 341</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id62db56d4-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id62db56d5-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="id62db56d6-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section was formerly classified to <ref href="/us/usc/t25/s494a">section 494a of this title</ref> prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as this section.</p>
</note>
</notes>
